`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"As such they have been widely employed for the study of many-body problems, which come originally from condensed matter. In the early stages this was used to study ground state properties of complex systems like unitary fermions or strongly correlated lattice systems. Importantly, experiments have gone well into the regime of non-perturbative theories. They are therefore well-established benchmarks for sophisticated numerical techniques, which would be otherwise uncontrolled."}),`
